.Dd September 21, 2002
.Dt NEED_RESCHED 9
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm need_resched
.Nd context switch notification
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/cpu.h
.Ft void
.Fn need_resched "struct cpu_info *ci"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn need_resched
function is the machine-independent interface for the scheduler to
notify machine-dependent code that a context switch from the current
process is required.
This event may occur if a higher priority process appears on the run
queue or if the current process has exceeded its time slice.
.Pp
Specifically, the
.Fn need_resched
function will perform the following operations:
.Bl -bullet -offset indent
.It
Set a global flag which is checked by
.Xr userret 9
when returning to user-mode execution.
.It
Post an asynchronous software trap (AST).
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr scheduler 9 ,
.Xr userret 9
